 fix this on my own, so I would really be<br />very grateful if somebody who has the hardware and the inclination would look<br />into it.<br /><br />(I looked into it just enough to see that it's ugly: the scatter-gather lists<br />used by the SCSI code use virtual addresses, and the aic7xx0 controller code<br />uses those scatter-gather lists directly. The high-level SCSI code would<br />either have to use bus addresses instead of virtual addresses, or the aic7xx0<br />driver should do the translation either on the CPU or in the aic7xx0<br />assembly). <br /><br />Most other drivers would seem to work, although some of them (like the xd<br />driver) haven't been tested. <br /><br />Other than the virtual kernel address setup changes on x86, the 2.1.0 release<br />also changes the VFS interface (lseek/read/write get longer types). There are<br />also quite a lot of m68k-specific changes (but I'm waiting with the generic<br />m68k changes until the driver situation has calmed down a bit). There is also<br />a tentative patch for the pty problems people have reported (that will be fed<br />back to the 2.0.x tree too, but you can test it out in the 2.1.x series<br />first)<br /><br />		Linus<br /><br /></pre><div align="center"><div class="shariff" data-services="[&quot;reddit&quot;]" data-theme="grey" data-lang="en" data-backend-url="//shariff.lkml.org/index.php"></div></div></td><td width="32" rowspan="2" class="c" valign="top"><img src="/images/icornerr.gif" width="32" height="32" alt="\" /></td></tr><tr><td align="right" valign="bottom">
